      "excerpt": "From ChatGPT to Grammarly, we tested the top AI writing tools. Find the perfect tool for blogs, emails, social media, and more.",
      "content": `AI writing tools have matured significantly. Whether you're drafting blog posts, writing marketing copy, or polishing emails, there's an AI writing tool that can accelerate your workflow.\n\nHere are our top 10 picks for 2026.\n\n## 1. ChatGPT\n\nThe most versatile AI assistant available. Handles everything from creative writing to email drafting to complex reasoning. Its free tier is remarkably generous.\n\n**Best for:** Everyone\n**Price:** Free tier available, Plus $20/month\n\n## 2. Claude\n\nClaude excels in long-form writing and deep reasoning with a massive 200,000-token context window. Ideal for researchers and writers who work with large documents.\n\n**Best for:** Researchers and writers\n**Price:** Free tier available, Pro $20/month\n\n## 3. Jasper\n\nJasper is built specifically for marketing teams with brand tone-of-voice features, comprehensive templates, and team collaboration.\n\n**Best for:** Marketing teams and agencies\n**Price:** Paid plans from $39/month\n\n## 4. Grammarly\n\nBest-in-class grammar checking with a browser extension that works everywhere. Essential for anyone who writes emails professionally.\n\n**Best for:** Everyone who writes emails\n**Price:** Free tier available, Premium $12/month\n\n## 5. Writesonic\n\nAI writing assistant with built-in SEO features and powerful article writer. Great value for SEO-focused content creators.\n\n**Best for:** SEO writers and bloggers\n**Price:** Free tier available\n\n## 6. Copy.ai\n\nOptimized for social media managers with extensive template library for posts, ads, and product descriptions.\n\n**Best for:** Social media managers\n**Price:** Free tier available\n\n## 7. QuillBot\n\nExcellent paraphrasing engine with multiple modes. Perfect for editors and students who need to rephrase existing content.\n\n**Best for:** Students and editors\n**Price:** Free tier available\n\n## 8. Perplexity AI\n\nAI-powered search engine with cited answers. Invaluable for research-intensive writing projects.\n\n**Best for:** Researchers and writers\n**Price:** Free tier available, Pro $20/month\n\n## 9. Sudowrite\n\nSpecialized for creative fiction with story brainstorming, character development, and scene expansion features.\n\n**Best for:** Fiction writers\n**Price:** Paid plans from $19/month\n\n## 10. Rytr\n\nOne of the most affordable AI writing tools with 40+ languages and 40+ templates. Great for budget-conscious creators.\n\n**Best for:** Budget-conscious creators\n**Price:** Free tier available, paid plans from $5/month\n\n## How to Choose\n\n- **General writing:** ChatGPT or Claude\n- **Marketing copy:** Jasper or Copy.ai\n- **Grammar and clarity:** Grammarly\n- **SEO content:** Writesonic\n- **Creative writing:** Sudowrite\n- **Research:** Perplexity AI`
